# Dev Environment — RHDP Instance Template

Copy this file to `docs/dev-environment.md` and fill in the values from your RHDP deployment.
`docs/dev-environment.md` is gitignored — never commit it.

## RHDP Catalog Item

**Introduction to AI-Driven Ansible Automation: Self-healing, Observability-Driven AIOps**
(provided by RHDP)

Order from the RHDP catalog, wait for provisioning to complete, then collect the URLs and
credentials from the RHDP instance details page.

---

## AAP

- **URL:** https://controller-<id>.apps.<cluster>.rhdp.net
- **Username:** admin
- **Password:** <aap-password>

## Mattermost

- **URL:** https://mattermost-<id>.apps.<cluster>.rhdp.net
- **Username:** ansibleadmin@ansible.com
- **Password:** <mattermost-password>
- **Team:** Automators
- **Channel:** Town Square

## Gitea

- **URL:** https://gitea-<id>.apps.<cluster>.rhdp.net
- **Username:** lab-user
- **Password:** <gitea-password>

## Splunk

- **URL:** https://splunk-<id>.apps.<cluster>.rhdp.net
- **Username:** admin
- **Password:** <splunk-password>
- **API Token:** <splunk-api-token>
  (created manually in Splunk UI: Settings → Tokens → New Token — first step of Part 2; see issue #1 for automation)

## SSH Bastion

- **Host:** ssh.<cluster>.rhdp.net
- **Port:** <bastion-port>
- **Username:** lab-user
- **Password:** <bastion-password>
- **Login:** `ssh lab-user@ssh.<cluster>.rhdp.net -p <bastion-port>`

## SSH (cisco-rtr1 — via bastion)

- **Internal IP:** <cisco-rtr1-internal-ip>
- **Username:** admin
- **Password:** <cisco-password>
- **Login:** `ssh -J lab-user@ssh.<cluster>.rhdp.net:<bastion-port> admin@<cisco-rtr1-internal-ip>`

## EDA Webhook

- **URL:** https://eda-webhook-<id>.apps.<cluster>.rhdp.net

## AI Inference (LiteLLM / Granite 3.2)

- **Endpoint:** https://litellm-prod.apps.maas.redhatworkshops.io/v1/completions
- **Model:** openai/granite-3-2-8b-instruct
- **Token:** stored in AAP credential — do not paste here
